<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="252" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[174,1233,276,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,356,340,366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Posterior notopleural, anepisternal, katepisternal, and anepimeral setae white, femora either entirely yellow (
<figureCitation box="[631,726,372,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[355,1053,1025,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-288@1.[331,1075,1015,1767]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–3. C. absinthi. 1 — ♀, habitus, right; 2 — mesonotum, dorsally; 3 — wing (SIZK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452426/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">fig. 1–2</figureCitation>
) or with basal one-third darkened; wing pattern rather pale, r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[420,447,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">2+3</subScript>
apex with one large spot, base of r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[859,886,423,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">4+5</subScript>
with large rounded spot; cell br with 2 hyaline rounded spots; stigma with one hyaline spot (
<figureCitation box="[930,993,436,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[355,1053,1025,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-288@1.[331,1075,1015,1767]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–3. C. absinthi. 1 — ♀, habitus, right; 2 — mesonotum, dorsally; 3 — wing (SIZK)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452426/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Phallus glans with thickened ovoid rostrum (
<bibRefCitation author="Korneyev, V. A. &amp; Ovtshinnikova, O. G." box="[490,873,468,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252" refId="ref4772" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Ovtshinnikova, O. G. 79. Fam. Tephritidae - Fruit Flies // Keys to Insects of Far East Russia. Vol. 6. Diptera and Fleas. Part 3 / Ed. A. S. Leley. - Vladivostok: Dal'nauka, 2004. - P. 456 - 564. - Russian: Koрнiiv V. A., Ovciннikova O. G. 79. Сiм. Tephritidae - мuki-piсtokрылki." type="book" year="2004">Korneyev, Ovtshinnikova, 2004</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 293, 
<emphasis box="[990,1004,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">3</emphasis>
). Oviscape shorter than 3 preceding abdominal tergites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="252" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[174,1233,276,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,369,532,558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is common in Europe, but very local in 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1053,533,559]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Larvae feed in flower heads of various wormwoods, first of all, absinth (
<taxonomicName box="[841,1065,564,591]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="absinthii">
<emphasis box="[841,1065,564,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Artemisia absinthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1232,564,591]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[1107,1232,564,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">A. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), which occur mainly in the North-Western 
<collectingCountry box="[723,776,597,623]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Iran</collectingCountry>
. See also comments on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1052,1167,596,623]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Campiglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="misella">
<emphasis box="[1052,1167,596,623]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">C. misella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
